<img class="aligncenter wp-image-1414510 size-large" src="https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/NSCDC.jpg?resize=640%2C344&#038;ssl=1" alt="NSCDC arrests 8 suspected kidnappers in Oyo" width="640" height="344" srcset="https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/NSCDC.jpg?resize=1024%2C550&amp;ssl=1 1024w, https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/NSCDC.jpg?resize=300%2C161&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/NSCDC.jpg?resize=768%2C412&amp;ssl=1 768w, https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/NSCDC.jpg?resize=58%2C31&amp;ssl=1 58w, https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/NSCDC.jpg?resize=260%2C140&amp;ssl=1 260w, https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/NSCDC.jpg?resize=200%2C107&amp;ssl=1 200w, https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/NSCDC.jpg?w=1300&amp;ssl=1 1300w" sizes="(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px" data-recalc-dims="1" /> The Nigeria Security and Civil Defence Corps (NSCDC) in Oyo State has arrested eight suspected kidnappers terrorising the people of Ado Awaye, Araromi, Okaka, Ilero and Otu in Itesiwsju Local Government Areas of the state. This was disclosed in a statement by the corps’ Public Relations Officer, Oluwole Olusegun, and made available to newsmen on Saturday in Ibadan. Olusegun quoted the Commandant of NSCDC in Oyo State, Iskilu Akinsanya, as saying that the suspects were apprehended by the Agro Rangers Squad of the command. Akinsanya said that the suspected kidnappers were arrested at about 9:15 pm on Thursday through information received from the Chief Jowuro of Oke-Ogun, Alhaji Baani Abubakar, that suspected kidnappers operating in the area were spotted in Bobajiroro Hotel, Oke Adeta, Iseyin. “The eight suspected kidnappers which consist of six males and two females were arrested at the Bobajiroro Hotel. ” During cross examination of the suspects, one of the trailed suspects to the scene of the arrest who was 25 years old, declared that the number used in tracking him belongs to his friend. “Further interrogation revealed that those numbers were stored on his phone with different codes such as 52,42,33, while the suspect later assisted the corps in apprehending the remaining seven suspects,” Akinsanya said. The News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) reports that items recovered from the suspects included two red Boxer Motorcycles marked BDJ 580 UL and EGB 628 UF, six cell phones and N32,510 cash. The commandant said that the suspects would be handed over to the Anti-Kidnapping Squad of the police in the state for further investigation and prosecution. NAN SECURITY agents in Ogun State are living up to their billing as they have arrested at least eight people whose crimes border on murder, kidnap and human rituals. April 25, 2014 In "News" By David Odama - Lafia No Fewer than twenty-eight suspected bandits, kidnappers, and armed robbery, including seven suspected assailants have been arrested by the men of the Nigeria Security and civil defense Corps (NSCDC), for allegedly killed nine persons in Nasarawa state. The State  commandant of the Corps, Dr. Muhammud… August 18, 2020 In "News" The Nigeria Security and Civil Defence Corps (NSCDC), Oyo State Command, has arrested three persons at Bolorundoro village in Orire Local Government Area for allegedly stealing two cows valued at N500,000. Mr Iskilu Akinsanya, the state Commandant of NSCDC, disclosed this to newsmen on Monday while parading the suspects at… July 28, 2020 In "News"